I think that most of the complainers here are clueless about what this actually is and how it works. This isn't Audible. It's never going to have new books like Harry Potter, but there's a reason for that:  The reason all the books are free is because THEY ARE ALL PUBLIC DOMAIN TITLES. That means that the books have to be old enough for their copyrights to expire. Harry Potter, Steven King, Tom Clancy, Hunger Games - these franchises and Authors are all still copyrighted and will be for a long, long time. It would be ILLEGAL to offer these books for free without the permission of the author or the author's estate. The thousands of classics that ARE available, however - Treasure Island, Sherlock Holmes, Three Musketeers, Alice in Wonderland, The Wizard of Oz - these are all stories whose copyrights have expired, and thus it is legal for anyone to print them, copy them, use their characters, etc.  The Librivox project takes UNPAID VOLUNTEERS and gets them to read these classic books. The recordings are then offered up in the public domain as well; which means that even though the readers are mostly all still alive and kicking, the recordings can dl'd and shared for free.
